    <h2>Keycaps</h2>
    <p>
        These are not as interesting as nor complex as switches can be, but there are two types: ABS and PBT. ABS is smoother and wear off faster, wherease PBT is "grippier" and lasts longer. Though not as complex,
        keycaps are the first thing everyone will notice about your keyboard, so make 'em good. There are also different profiles for keycaps like Cherry, XVX, low; but they are not as drastic of a change as switches are.
    </p>

